        start_npc = 'Ryoma',
        start_zone = 'Norg',
        start_pos = 'H-8',
        description = 'The trick box you brought back to Norg has been identified as a fake. Your assistance is required in finding the real box. Start your search by pressing Ensetsu in Bastok for more information.',
        reward = 'Ninja Hakama',
        fame = 'Other',
        fame_level = '1',
        title = nil,
        repeatable = 'Yes',
        previous = {'20 in Pirate Years'},
        next = {
            'True Will',
            'Borghertz\'s Lurking Hands',
        },
        requirements = {
            {name = 'Oak Pole', count = 1},
        },
        walkthrough = '1. Travel to Norg and speak with Ryoma to receive the quest.\n   - If you just completed 20 in Pirate Years you will need to zone and re-enter Norg for Ryoma to begin this quest\n2. Talk to Ensetsu in Port Bastok at (I-5), who tells you to speak with Leodarion.\n3. Head to Rabao and talk to Leodarion at (F-8) on the west side of the lake near the windmill.\n4. Leodarion will request an Oak Pole, which is purchasable via Sparks from a Records of Eminence NPC:\n   - Rolandienne in Southern San d\'Oria (G-10)\n   - Isakoth in Bastok Markets (E-11)\n   - Fhelm Jobeizat in Windurst Woods (J-10)\n   - Eternal Flame in Western Adoulin (H-11)\n     - Costs 156 Sparks. Can be found under "Equ. Lv. 40 - 50.", on Page 2.\n5. After trading it to him, speak to Leodarion again on the next Vana\'diel day. You will receive the [Key Item]Seance staff with instructions to travel to Mhaura.\n6. Once in Mhaura, take the ferry to Selbina so that you will be traveling at nighttime.\n   - Suitable ferry departure times for this quest leave Mhaura at 16:00 and 0:00.\n7. The NM Enagakure will spawn on the main deck.\n   - On the ferry departing at 0:00, it will already be on the deck and will disappear at 4:00.\n   - On the ferry departing at 16:00, you must wait for night time at 20:00 for it to appear.\n   - Make sure you have unloaded FastCS, as they will cause you to be booted straight to Selbina if zoning into the Mhaura-Selbina Ferry at night.\n8. Once you have defeated Enagakure, make sure you have at least one inventory slot free and wait until the ferry docks in Selbina.\n9. You will receive a cutscene, Ninja Hakama, and the quest will be complete.',
        notes = nil,
    },
